race.comment: TARPAULIN (2) was quickly into stride and went on to score by 8 lengths last time out over 1207m at Saratoga (Dirt). Stepping up a level this time but on his best form he is one of the key runners. FLYING LIAM (7) is back from a spell of four-and-a-half months. Closed last campaign with a minor placing over 1106m at Monmouth Park (Dirt). Strong chance to kick the campaign off on the right note. CRUSHED IT (4) failed to threaten when fresh from a spell last time out, beaten 8 lengths into sixth over 1609m at Saratoga (Dirt). Should park just off the speed. One of the main contenders. MIGHTY ATLAS (3) hasn't been able to break through for an extended period, the latest effort a sixth over 1609m at this track (Dirt). This is a nice drop in grade so he is one of the main contenders.
